./sdp/logs/Lead_frac-0029_1777721353.log:361:./sdp/logs/Verify_T-010_20260416T181925Z_1776384834.log:8650:+{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-04-16T21:36:47.681Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1776375407681_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-023@20260416T054258Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** Gemini CLI\n**Date:** 2026-04-16\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/self_critique.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/senseweave/tracker_compiler.py`\n- `my-claw/tools/duet_composer.py`\n- `tests/test_course_critique.py`\n- `specs/t-023@20260416t054258z-spec.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation strictly follows the technical approach outlined in the specification. `COURSE_METRIC_MAP` correctly maps course concepts to metric thresholds. `thresholds_for_course` merges these overrides into defaults, preferring stricter thresholds. `critique_score_with_course` provides detailed failure attribution naming the failing course concept. `revision_targets_from_failures` correctly identifies which musical dimensions should be adjusted based on the failures.\n\n## Completeness\nAll aspects of the task are complete. The system handles missing `production_course` metadata gracefully by falling back to defaults. The integration into both `tracker_compiler` and `duet_composer` ensures comprehensive coverage of the composition pipeline. The test suite covers all acceptance criteria, including end-to-end revision and metric improvement.\n\n## Consistency\nThe code follows established patterns in the `senseweave` toolset. It uses the existing `ear_engine` metrics and integrates seamlessly with `generative_scores`. The use of dataclasses for reports and targets is consistent with the codebase's style.\n\n## Security\nNo security issues were identified. The changes are local to the musical analysis and revision logic and do not involve sensitive data or unsafe practices.\n\n## Quality\nThe implementation is high-quality, with clear separation of concerns. The tests are comprehensive and provide good coverage of both unit and integration scenarios. The `CourseCritiqueReport` and `RevisionTargets` provide useful structured data for debugging and future enhancements.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n- The hardening item regarding `bootstrap_identity` was confirmed to be addressed in `cypherclaw_daemon.py` and `daemon.py`.\n- All 56 critique tests (31 new + 25 existing) passed successfully.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-023@20260416t054258z-verify.md"}}
