CHANGELOG.md:5:- Added depth-2 quota-aware agent selector end-to-end test coverage (frac-0057): `tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py` now ships a new `TestAgentSelectorEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public selector surface (`AgentSelector.select`, `select_pair`, `detect_category`, `record_outcome`, `status_summary`) through looped end-to-end methods. The new tests walk an alternation/rotation cycle across eight selects, round-trip selector state through `state_file` between two `AgentSelector` instances, sweep a category-detection table covering architecture/coding/review/research/testing/devops/netops/writing/routing/narrative_prose, run an Ollama health-recovery cycle (healthy → unhealthy → healthy) against the real `QuotaMonitor`, exercise pair selection across the default provider set, validate that `status_summary` lists every default agent and quota provider with mixed health statuses, confirm `disabled_agents` filtering is per-call rather than persistent across a sequence, sweep headrooms to flip the winner between providers, run `record_outcome` safely without an observatory across many calls, and verify that `select` raises `ValueError` when every available agent is disabled. `tests/test_agent_selector_quota_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `TestAgentSelectorQuota` assertions and `agent_selector` / `quota_monitor` / `ollama_health` source modules remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
